location.name: PN Jeannette Kawas--Sector Miami a Barra Vieja

mediaNotes:
Sounds heard as the bird flew overhead in the dark. Later the same bird (or possibly another) flew over, 100-400 feet away. 

ML: Originally catalogued as Nycticorax violaceus; changed per AOU 7th ed. Habitat: Swamp.

Nesting colony that also included the following: Black-crowned Night-heron, Great Egret, Snowy Egret, Glossy Ibis, Great Blue Heron, Green Heron. When a Yellow-crowned Night-heron flew out away from the colony, an attempt was made to follow it with the parabola. One or two faint calls in the background are unidentified. The colony is young (known only to the refuge for 2-3 years).
